    {
      "id": "333716b2732cf05e2dc8b601f9f0feaab6fc57fb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2016-12-13 22:34:44.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(4 comments)\n\nLooks like the update to the lfs getdirstripe usage message does not match what is actually implemented for lfs_getstripe_internal().  Possibly there is some confusion between lfs_getdirstripe() and lfs_setdirstripe()?\n\nThat said, having the \"--mdt-hash\" option would definitely be useful (e.g. to locate directories that are in the middle of migration).\n\nRunning \"lfs getdirstripe --mdt-hash\" for a non-striped directory should print something useful like \"none\" or similar, instead of returning an error.  Also desirable would be making an array of LMV_HASH_TYPE_* -> name mappings and looping through those when parsing stripe_hash_opt in lfs_setdirstripe() instead of a large if/else block.\n\nPlease also verify that the '-t' option does not conflict with PFL.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
